  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "Removing a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list can help declutter your conversations and enhance your privacy. Below are the steps to accomplish this on both **mobile devices (iOS and Android)** and the **desktop/web version** of Facebook Messenger.\n\n---\n\n### **For Mobile Devices (iOS and Android):**\n\n1. **Open the Messenger App:**\n   - Launch the **Facebook Messenger** app on your smartphone.\n\n2. **Access Your Contacts/People List:**\n   - Tap on your **profile picture** in the top left corner to access settings.\n   - Alternatively, you might see a **\"People\"** or **\"Contacts\"** tab at the bottom or side menu, depending on your app version.\n\n3. **Find the Non-Friend You Want to Remove:**\n   - Scroll through your contacts list or use the **search bar** at the top to locate the person.\n\n4. **Open Their Profile:**\n   - Tap on the person's name to open their **Messenger profile**.\n\n5. **Remove or Block the Contact:**\n   - **To Remove from Contacts:**\n     - Look for an option like **\"Remove from Contacts\"** or **\"Unmatch\"** (if applicable). Note that Messenger doesn't have a direct \"remove\" feature for all contacts, especially non-friends, so removing the conversation might suffice.\n   - **To Delete the Conversation:**\n     - Go back to the main Messenger screen.\n     - **Swipe left** on the conversation you wish to delete.\n     - Tap on the **trash can icon** or **\"Delete\"** option.\n   - **To Block the Contact:**\n     - Open their Messenger profile.\n     - Scroll down and tap on **\"Block\"**.\n     - Confirm by selecting **\"Block on Messenger\"**.\n     - *Blocking ensures they no longer appear in your contacts and cannot message you.*\n\n---\n\n### **For Desktop/Web Version:**\n\n1. **Open Messenger:**\n   - Go to [Messenger.com](https://www.messenger.com/) or open Facebook and click on the **Messenger** icon.\n\n2. **Access Your Contacts List:**\n   - Click on the **\"People\"** section or the **\"Contacts\"** tab within Messenger.\n\n3. **Locate the Non-Friend:**\n   - Browse through your list or use the **search bar** to find the person you wish to remove.\n\n4. **Open the Conversation:**\n   - Click on the person's name to open the chat window.\n\n5. **Remove or Block the Contact:**\n   - **To Delete the Conversation:**\n     - Click on the **three dots (\u22ef)** in the top right corner of the chat window.\n     - Select **\"Delete\"** or **\"Delete Conversation\"**.\n     - Confirm the deletion. *Note: This action removes the conversation from your inbox but doesn\u2019t prevent the person from messaging you again.*\n   - **To Block the Contact:**\n     - In the chat window, click on the **\"i\"** (information) icon.\n     - Scroll down and click **\"Block\"**.\n     - Choose **\"Block on Messenger\"** and confirm.\n     - *Blocking stops the person from contacting you and removes them from your contacts list.*\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Archiving Conversations:** If you prefer not to permanently delete a conversation, you can **archive** it. This moves the conversation out of your main inbox without deleting it.\n  \n  - **Mobile:** Swipe left on the conversation and select **\"Archive\"**.\n  - **Desktop:** Hover over the conversation, click the three dots (\u22ef), and choose **\"Archive\"**.\n\n- **Adjusting Message Settings:** To prevent non-friends from messaging you in the future:\n  \n  1. **Open Messenger Settings:**\n     - Tap or click on your **profile picture**.\n  \n  2. **Navigate to Privacy Settings:**\n     - Select **\"Privacy\"** or **\"Message Delivery\"**.\n  \n  3. **Adjust Who Can Send You Messages:**\n     - Set preferences to limit messages to **friends** or **specific groups**.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively remove non-friends from your Facebook Messenger contact list, ensuring a more streamlined and secure messaging experience.\n\n---\n\nIf you encounter any issues or if the interface has changed (as platforms frequently update their layouts), consider checking the [Facebook Help Center](https://www.facebook.com/help/) for the most up-to-date instructions.",
